</taxonomicName>
] (both 
<taxonomicName id="00DB99B1FF921921544DFD3F5FA1FD10" box="[264,411,738,762]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Onagraceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Onagraceae</taxonomicName>
) (
<bibRefCitation id="A34A9FC3FF92192154F4FD3F5C06FD10" author="Blake, D. H." box="[433,572,738,762]" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" pagination="9 - 29" refId="ref26189" refString="Blake, D. H. 1964. Notes on new and old species of Alticinae (Coleoptera) from the West Indies. Proceedings of the United States National Museum 115 (3477): 9 - 29." type="journal article" year="1964">Blake 1964</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="A34A9FC3FF9219215702FD3F5DF8FD10" author="Virkki, N. &amp; J. A. Santiago-Blay" box="[583,962,738,762]" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" pagination="79 - 99" refId="ref28398" refString="Virkki, N., and J. A. Santiago-Blay. 1994. Chromosomes of some neotropical flea beetles (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae: Alticinae) with inherently univalent, amphiorientating sex chromosomes and meioformula 11 + X + y in the male meiosis. Cytobios 80: 79 - 99." type="journal article" year="1994">Virkki and Santiago-Blay 1994</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="A34A9FC3FF9219215689FD3F5A36FD10" author="Virkki, N. &amp; J. A. Santiago-Blay" box="[972,1036,738,762]" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" pagination="69 - 83" refId="ref28451" refString="Virkki, N., and J. A. Santiago-Blay. 1998. Chromosome numbers in 71 Puerto Rican species of leaf beetles (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae). Journal of Agriculture of the University of Puerto Rico 82 (1 - 2): 69 - 83." type="journal article" year="1998">1998</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8FC1B1B9FF9219215585FCFF5C3BFC30" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C764E232FF9219215585FCFF5C3BFC30" blockId="19.[192,1440,802,986]" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis id="F5AF3E20FF9219215585FCFF5F60FCD0" bold="true" box="[192,346,802,826]" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Comments.</emphasis>
In recent years, this species has been treated in the genus 
<taxonomicName id="00DB99B1FF921921514DFCFF5B24FCD0" authority="Bechyne. This" authorityName="Bechyne. This" box="[1032,1310,802,826]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Lysathia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F5AF3E20FF921921514DFCFF5A4BFCD0" box="[1032,1137,802,826]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Lysathia</emphasis>
Bechyné. This
</taxonomicName>
placement may have been extrapolated from 
<bibRefCitation id="A34A9FC3FF921921571BFC9F5D37FCB0" author="Blake, D. H." box="[606,781,834,858]" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" pagination="9 - 29" refId="ref26189" refString="Blake, D. H. 1964. Notes on new and old species of Alticinae (Coleoptera) from the West Indies. Proceedings of the United States National Museum 115 (3477): 9 - 29." type="journal article" year="1964">Blake’s (1964)</bibRefCitation>
statement that, “It is of the same elongate shape as 
<taxonomicName id="00DB99B1FF92192150C3FC9E5FBDFC90" authority="Fall" authorityName="Fall" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Asclepias" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ludoviciana">
<emphasis id="F5AF3E20FF92192150C3FC9E5F6AFC90" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">A. ludoviciana</emphasis>
Fall
</taxonomicName>
” (
<taxonomicName id="00DB99B1FF92192154E7FCBF5CBAFC90" box="[418,640,866,890]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Altica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ludoviciana">
<emphasis id="F5AF3E20FF92192154E7FCBF5CBAFC90" box="[418,640,866,890]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Altica ludoviciana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is now correctly placed in 
<taxonomicName id="00DB99B1FF92192156F8FCBF5A12FC90" box="[957,1064,866,890]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Lysathia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F5AF3E20FF92192156F8FCBF5A12FC90" box="[957,1064,866,890]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Lysathia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Although Blake’s comment is true, the two species, other than shape, are quite different. Suffrian’s species should be returned to 
<taxonomicName id="00DB99B1FF921921501CFC5F5F46FC50" authority="Geoffroy. Based" authorityName="Geoffroy. Based" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Altica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F5AF3E20FF921921501CFC5F5B9AFC70" box="[1369,1440,898,922]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Altica</emphasis>
Geoffroy. Based
</taxonomicName>
mostly on characters of the male genitalia, José Santisteban (personal communication) concurs with this opinion.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
